definitions.definition: A state of long-standing mutual hostility .
examples: You couldn't call it a feud exactly, but there had always been a chill between Phil Mickelson and Tiger Woods .

definitions.definition: ( professional wrestling ) A staged rivalry between wrestlers.
( obsolete ) A combination of kindred to avenge injuries or affronts, done or offered to any of their blood, on the offender and all his race.
